<a name="extra-disciplinarycourses"></a>
<h3>Extra-Disciplinary Courses</h3>




<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-2908bd12-7fff-da3d-f825-db1542721f61">The Extra-Disciplinary requirement ensures that students also engage with cognitive scientific work outside the core disciplines, in areas such as music, anthropology, religion, economics, and political science, and so are exposed to the full breadth of the interdisciplinary study of the mind. Students in the major must take a total of two Extra-Disciplinary courses.</span></p>




<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-2908bd12-7fff-da3d-f825-db1542721f61">A partial list of courses that could be used to satisfy the Extra-Disciplinary requirement is provided below; as above, students may also request approval of courses not included in this list, or courses from other fields, by submitting a proposal and rationale to the Director of the Cognitive Science Program.</span></p>




